\subsection{Host} \label{ComputeHost}


  		





  
  93
  
    
\subsection{ExecutionHost} \label{ComputeHost}


  		





  94
  94
  
    

  		





  95
  
  
    
This property is a container for various information about the host where the user consumed the resource.  As an example, in case of MPI processes, more than one \emph{Host} property can be specified. 


  		





  
  95
  
    
This property is a container for various information about the host where the application was executed.  As an example, in case of MPI processes, more than one \emph{ExecutionHost} property can be specified. 


  		





  96
  96
  
    
\begin{itemize}


  		





  97
  
  
    
\item \emph{Host} MAY be present multiple times.


  		





  98
  
  
    
\item \emph{Host} MUST NOT have a value.


  		





  99
  
  
    
\item \emph{Host} MUST contain at least one value.


  		





  
  97
  
    
\item \emph{ExecutionHost} MAY be present multiple times.


  		





  
  98
  
    
\item \emph{ExecutionHost} MUST NOT have a value.


  		





  
  99
  
    
\item \emph{ExecutionHost} MUST contain at least one value.


  		





  100
  100
  
    
\end{itemize}


  		





  101
  101
  
    

  		





  102
  102
  
    
\begin{XMLexample}


  		





  103
  
  
    
<ur:Host>


  		





  
  103
  
    
<ur:ExecutionHost>


  		





  104
  104
  
    
  <!-- Various host properties go in here -->


  		





  105
  
  
    
</ur:Host>


  		





  
  105
  
    
</ur:ExecutionHost>


  		





  106
  106
  
    
\end{XMLexample}


  		





  107
  107
  
    

  		





  108
  108
  
    
\subsubsection{Hostname}


  		





  109
  109
  
    

  		





  110
  
  
    
The name of the \emph{Host}.


  		





  
  110
  
    
The name of the \emph{ExecutionHost}.


  		





  111
  111
  
    
\begin{itemize}


  		





  112
  112
  
    
\item \emph{Hostname} MUST be a string.


  		





  113
  
  
    
\item \emph{Hostname} MUST be under \emph{Host}.


  		





  114
  
  
    
\item \emph{Hostname} MUST be present if \emph{Host} is present.


  		





  
  113
  
    
\item \emph{Hostname} MUST be under \emph{ExecutionHost}.


  		





  
  114
  
    
\item \emph{Hostname} MUST be present if \emph{ExecutionHost} is present.


  		





  115
  115
  
    
\item The attribute \emph{primary} MAY be present in this element.


  		





  116
  116
  
    
\item The attribute \emph{primary} MUST be a boolean.


  		





  117
  117
  
    
\end{itemize}
